1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,820
The most entertaining suspense
that predicts love.

2
00:00:02,820 --> 00:00:04,570
Love line prediction game, Heart Signal.

3
00:00:04,570 --> 00:00:09,690
Five people with sharp romance radars
have gathered.

4
00:00:10,570 --> 00:00:13,350
- Here we are.
- Last week,

5
00:00:13,350 --> 00:00:15,310
they had nickname dates.

6
00:00:15,310 --> 00:00:17,200
That was crazy.

7
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:21,690
Min Ju chose Busy Hamster
and had a date with Seong Min.

8
00:00:21,690 --> 00:00:23,990
Kim Min Ju was truly a bulldozer.

9
00:00:23,990 --> 00:00:27,590
I don't think she was like,
"I still like you, Oppa."

10
00:00:27,590 --> 00:00:29,340
Are you kidding me?

11
00:00:29,340 --> 00:00:31,250
Her hands were trembling when she talked.

12
00:00:31,250 --> 00:00:32,360
She still likes him a lot.

13
00:00:32,360 --> 00:00:34,700
I know. She gave him a plant, too.

14
00:00:34,700 --> 00:00:37,850
Seong Min also had a date
with Yu Gyeong the next day.

15
00:00:37,850 --> 00:00:40,570
Seong Min must still have feelings
for Yu Gyeong.

16
00:00:40,570 --> 00:00:42,270
- Right.
- He can't move on from that.

17
00:00:42,270 --> 00:00:44,360
But Yu Gyeong texted Seong Min.

18
00:00:44,360 --> 00:00:46,960
But she's always been consistent.

19
00:00:46,960 --> 00:00:52,220
She's been texting someone she spent
most of her time with to be polite.

20
00:00:52,220 --> 00:00:54,610
She's been doing that consistently.

21
00:00:54,610 --> 00:00:56,780
Wu Yeol couldn't have slept that night.

22
00:00:56,780 --> 00:01:02,090
He must've thought
that he had to message Gyu Ri.

23
00:01:02,090 --> 00:01:05,280
But unfortunately,
he didn't get a single text.

24
00:01:05,280 --> 00:01:07,600
I've never seen him with that expression.

25
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:09,870
And Seo Won and So Yun's improvised date.

26
00:01:09,870 --> 00:01:11,690
- It was very upbeat.
- It was nice.

27
00:01:11,690 --> 00:01:14,120
I'm all for this couple.

28
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:16,890
I love how honest So Yun is.

29
00:01:16,890 --> 00:01:21,190
So Yun will probably express her feelings
for Seo Won a few more times.

30
00:01:21,190 --> 00:01:22,280
Right, right.

31
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:23,860
I can't wait to watch it.

32
00:01:23,860 --> 00:01:26,400
They exchanged heartfelt texts that evening.

33
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:29,580
Let's see what happened in Signal House.

34
00:01:29,580 --> 00:01:32,370
[On the way home after the date]

35
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:43,410
You're back on the route you were on.

36
00:01:44,930 --> 00:01:47,430
Do you think you have found your ideal type?

37
00:01:47,430 --> 00:01:49,140
Ideal type?

38
00:01:49,140 --> 00:01:50,940
Gosh.

39
00:01:55,800 --> 00:02:02,560
[Episode 11: The Wall of Truth]

40
00:02:03,290 --> 00:02:05,330
Hi.

41
00:02:09,020 --> 00:02:11,260
You seem happy about everything.

42
00:02:11,260 --> 00:02:12,470
Take these slippers, Noona.

43
00:02:12,470 --> 00:02:15,090
- My gosh!
- Hold on.

44
00:02:15,090 --> 00:02:16,720
Hold on.

45
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:18,810
I'm sorry.

46
00:02:18,810 --> 00:02:22,050
- Are you okay?
- Are you okay? Are you hurt?

47
00:02:22,050 --> 00:02:24,720
- I'm sorry. I shouldn't have closed it.
- Are you okay?

48
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:26,930
You drank, didn't you?

49
00:02:26,930 --> 00:02:28,770
No, I didn't. I didn't.

50
00:02:28,770 --> 00:02:32,030
Nothing happened. Nothing happened.
Nothing happened.

51
00:02:32,030 --> 00:02:33,630
Put these on.

52
00:02:34,410 --> 00:02:37,240
What's with you today? You look so hip.

53
00:02:52,940 --> 00:02:54,360
[Looking]

54
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:55,990
[Looking]

55
00:02:55,990 --> 00:02:58,970
You always look at me like this.

56
00:02:58,970 --> 00:03:00,920
You could just turn like this.

57
00:03:01,740 --> 00:03:04,910
I looked because I thought
you were looking at me.

58
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:12,040
You couldn't even make eye contact at first.

59
00:03:12,950 --> 00:03:13,950
Huh?

60
00:03:14,550 --> 00:03:19,110
[Their first date]

61
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:24,070
He can't make eye contact.

62
00:03:25,210 --> 00:03:28,160
Do you know you avoided eye contact with me?

63
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:31,140
I don't know. I don't remember.

64
00:03:31,780 --> 00:03:33,610
I'm a slow starter.

65
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:38,760
But now, you blatantly look at me.

66
00:03:46,780 --> 00:03:48,880
Do you have monolids?

67
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:51,650
- Hidden double eyelids?
- No.

68
00:03:51,650 --> 00:03:53,940
I have double eyelids.
Can you not see them?

69
00:03:53,940 --> 00:03:55,290
[Leaning over]

70
00:04:04,820 --> 00:04:06,800
I probably looked like
I had monolids yesterday.

71
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,330
Because you were tired?

72
00:04:08,330 --> 00:04:11,810
No, I was wearing more makeup.

73
00:04:13,670 --> 00:04:16,390
Don't I look different from yesterday?

74
00:04:16,390 --> 00:04:18,420
- You?
- Yes.

75
00:04:22,180 --> 00:04:23,040
[Glancing]

76
00:04:24,310 --> 00:04:25,940
- What?
- Huh?

77
00:04:25,940 --> 00:04:27,280
- What?
- What do you mean?

78
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:29,180
- You just looked at me.
- I didn't.

79
00:04:29,180 --> 00:04:30,790
Okay, got it.

80
00:04:30,790 --> 00:04:32,320
[Looking]

81
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:36,040
I pretended I was looking.

82
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:38,690
I love this dynamic.

83
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:45,110
You're so funny, Noona.

84
00:04:45,110 --> 00:04:47,530
Me? Why?

85
00:04:48,740 --> 00:04:50,670
Do I need a reason for finding you funny?

86
00:04:50,670 --> 00:04:51,950
How about me?

87
00:04:51,950 --> 00:04:53,530
You're funny.

88
00:04:54,530 --> 00:04:56,400
That's what I was saying.

89
00:04:58,540 --> 00:05:01,800
- He seems to be falling for her.
- He has.

90
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:05,640
[Yesterday's Self Talk]

91
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:09,680
[Who hurt your feelings the most today?]

92
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:11,900
So Yun...

93
00:05:13,660 --> 00:05:16,010
seems to be having a hard time.

94
00:05:16,010 --> 00:05:19,680
She was the last one to join.

95
00:05:20,710 --> 00:05:25,820
She must have been confused
by going on three dates the next day.

96
00:05:26,590 --> 00:05:30,360
She probably didn't get to know people well.

97
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:34,520
But finding out their opinions
must have confused her.

98
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:35,690
Gosh.

99
00:05:35,690 --> 00:05:41,210
I find courage like that so admirable.

100
00:05:41,210 --> 00:05:46,000
Not anyone could've done the same.
I couldn't have, either.

101
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,100
Her ideal man is a good gamer.

102
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:50,100
- Really?
- Really.

103
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:51,440
What are you doing on Friday?

104
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,540
What are you doing on Friday?

105
00:05:52,540 --> 00:05:53,760
What are you doing?

106
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:56,100
I want to go out to eat with you.

107
00:05:56,900 --> 00:05:58,760
[She's direct]

108
00:06:00,670 --> 00:06:02,480
[She knows how to have fun]

109
00:06:03,130 --> 00:06:03,960
[Dropping]

110
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:05,470
[She's clumsy]

111
00:06:05,470 --> 00:06:07,160
I didn't see that.

112
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,830
[And she makes him worry]

113
00:06:12,470 --> 00:06:17,100
I always think before I text someone.

114
00:06:29,290 --> 00:06:31,780
That's a suggestive look.

115
00:06:34,940 --> 00:06:39,020
I think So Yun is the one who's
breaking my heart the most now.

116
00:06:39,020 --> 00:06:41,060
Gosh.

117
00:06:42,460 --> 00:06:45,360
- Living together does a lot, doesn't it?
- Huh?

118
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:48,570
Living together is the biggest
reason why your feelings grow.

119
00:06:48,570 --> 00:06:49,550
You're right.

120
00:06:49,550 --> 00:06:51,550
It's an unusual circumstance.

121
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:55,480
I'm so confused.

122
00:06:57,800 --> 00:07:05,300
[What emotion is he going through?]

123
00:07:15,620 --> 00:07:18,550
- Do I look funny?
- I'm joking.

124
00:07:21,860 --> 00:07:23,030
[She couldn't hide her feelings]

125
00:07:23,030 --> 00:07:25,040
Oh, my God.

126
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:27,770
Have you been in unrequited love?

127
00:07:28,430 --> 00:07:29,790
Unrequited love?

128
00:07:29,790 --> 00:07:31,460
[Staring]

129
00:07:31,460 --> 00:07:34,710
I have...

130
00:07:34,710 --> 00:07:37,080
[Day 12]

131
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:38,960
Hi.

132
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:41,670
- I just got home.
- Why did you come in so silently?

133
00:07:41,670 --> 00:07:43,140
I remember.

134
00:07:43,140 --> 00:07:46,310
Seo Won was making ramen
alone in the kitchen.

135
00:07:46,310 --> 00:07:49,930
I made eye contact with him then.

136
00:07:49,930 --> 00:07:53,580
For the first time, I thought,
"Was he always this handsome?"

137
00:07:53,580 --> 00:07:55,110
Oh, really?

138
00:07:55,110 --> 00:07:58,920
- How can you not fall for him?
- It's impossible.

139
00:08:01,940 --> 00:08:03,530
This is nice.

140
00:08:03,530 --> 00:08:06,160
It's nice to be welcomed by everyone.

141
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:10,380
I wrote down the dinner menu
because I had nothing to do.

142
00:08:10,380 --> 00:08:11,510
I'm glad you did.

143
00:08:11,510 --> 00:08:13,690
Did you write that?

144
00:08:13,690 --> 00:08:15,620
- You wrote the question?
- So cute.

145
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:16,810
[So Yun asked what they wanted for dinner]

146
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:19,880
Yes, I'm the one who asked.

147
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:24,300
You're not very observant.
There were seven Post-it notes.

148
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:26,840
I'm so touched that he noticed.

149
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:29,620
- What?
- That your answer was missing?

150
00:08:29,620 --> 00:08:32,190
I noticed it immediately.
You have pretty handwriting.

151
00:08:32,190 --> 00:08:35,050
[Seo Won immediately knew it was So Yun]

152
00:08:36,260 --> 00:08:37,970
He keeps fluttering her heart.

153
00:08:37,970 --> 00:08:40,520
For me...

154
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:45,620
every time I was in unrequited love,

155
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,930
I ended up with them.

156
00:08:49,950 --> 00:08:53,430
[Thinking of one person after that comment]

157
00:08:54,130 --> 00:08:58,390
[Seo Won's 90%]

158
00:08:59,550 --> 00:09:00,980
I agree.

159
00:09:03,340 --> 00:09:04,850
My gosh.

160
00:09:04,850 --> 00:09:08,130
I've always been at 100%, and the
other was at 0% in the beginning.

161
00:09:09,380 --> 00:09:11,520
Or 99% versus 1%.

162
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:13,560
"I like you. I like you. I like you."

163
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,690
Wow.

164
00:09:22,140 --> 00:09:24,850
She crossed a line she can't come back from.

165
00:09:26,540 --> 00:09:28,540
I'll stop by upstairs, too.

166
00:09:30,110 --> 00:09:31,540
Okay.

167
00:09:40,790 --> 00:09:42,840
What? Is everyone going upstairs?

168
00:09:51,310 --> 00:09:55,630
[A very dark night]

169
00:09:57,750 --> 00:09:59,890
What a mess.

170
00:10:00,530 --> 00:10:04,670
If I get a chance to volunteer tomorrow,

171
00:10:04,670 --> 00:10:07,400
- I'd like to cook.
- Really?

172
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:10,480
I might make something elaborate. Galbijjim?

173
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:13,110
[Wu Yeol: Galbijjim, chicken, sushi...]

174
00:10:13,110 --> 00:10:14,990
This is crazy.

175
00:10:14,990 --> 00:10:16,600
Galbijjim?

176
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,860
Should we get going now?

177
00:10:21,860 --> 00:10:23,210
Okay.

178
00:10:25,340 --> 00:10:27,320
Look at his face.

179
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:32,800
Weren't you ever worried
about looking way too close

180
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:35,360
to just one person?

181
00:10:37,130 --> 00:10:42,640
I thought I was good
at detecting those things.

182
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:46,230
It was brought up playfully.

183
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:50,010
But I think...

184
00:10:51,810 --> 00:10:55,270
I was slow to notice it then.

185
00:10:58,140 --> 00:11:00,520
That's when I knew I messed up.

186
00:11:01,220 --> 00:11:04,230
She didn't seem to be having that much fun.

187
00:11:04,230 --> 00:11:07,440
After I noticed it that day,

188
00:11:08,350 --> 00:11:10,140
I became very worried.

189
00:11:10,140 --> 00:11:16,490
I think I was only focused
on Yu Gyeong at the time.

190
00:11:16,490 --> 00:11:23,260
I wasn't really worried about anyone else.

191
00:11:23,260 --> 00:11:25,440
He's honest now.

192
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:31,770
Here they are. Here they are.

193
00:11:31,770 --> 00:11:33,130
Hi.

194
00:11:33,130 --> 00:11:35,660
[Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri are home]

195
00:11:37,970 --> 00:11:40,800
Start briefing, everyone. Who's going first?

196
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,860
Okay, okay.

197
00:11:42,860 --> 00:11:44,540
Where did you go?

198
00:11:44,540 --> 00:11:46,440
We're competing with each other.

199
00:11:47,580 --> 00:11:51,190
It looks like you just came home.

200
00:11:55,590 --> 00:11:57,980
What did you do? Did you drink?

201
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:02,050
What did you do?

202
00:12:02,050 --> 00:12:03,580
Do you want to sit?

203
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:05,650
I won't tell you, either.

204
00:12:05,650 --> 00:12:07,580
No, we are in a different situation.

205
00:12:07,580 --> 00:12:09,530
How so? We went to Gangneung.

206
00:12:09,530 --> 00:12:12,020
- Why would you tell them that?
- Really?

207
00:12:12,020 --> 00:12:13,530
I was in Tokyo.

208
00:12:13,530 --> 00:12:15,750
- You were where?
- Tokyo.

209
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:18,580
- You're not going to work tomorrow?
- No, I'm so happy.

210
00:12:18,580 --> 00:12:20,760
You finally get to sleep in.

211
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,230
I'm so happy.

212
00:12:22,230 --> 00:12:27,970
I want to be in bed feeling like this.

213
00:12:55,010 --> 00:12:56,860
What did you do today?

214
00:13:02,230 --> 00:13:04,130
You're a bit different today.

215
00:13:05,690 --> 00:13:07,250
You're right.

216
00:13:07,250 --> 00:13:09,560
You look like you just moved in.

217
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:12,920
- The tweed jacket?
- He doesn't care about anyone else.

218
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:17,060
So, what did you do?

219
00:13:18,390 --> 00:13:20,310
I don't know.

220
00:13:20,310 --> 00:13:22,300
Why is everyone talking about their date?

221
00:13:22,300 --> 00:13:24,410
You guys did something, didn't you?

222
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:31,850
- He's jealous.
- I played my guitar at home for some reason.

223
00:13:31,850 --> 00:13:34,300
Really? Why are you dressed like this, then?

224
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:36,630
He wants to know.

225
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:39,050
Didn't you go on a date?

226
00:13:42,890 --> 00:13:46,020
- She said it's a secret.
- I was on a date by myself.

227
00:13:51,740 --> 00:13:53,810
What did you eat?

228
00:13:53,810 --> 00:13:55,130
- Me?
- Yes.

229
00:13:55,130 --> 00:13:57,410
- I had chicken kalguksu.
- Sounds good.

230
00:13:58,120 --> 00:14:00,400
- Are you wearing your own clothes?
- Of course.

231
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:02,200
- Really?
- Yup.

232
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:05,010
- I'll put my head down.
- Gosh.

233
00:14:45,290 --> 00:14:50,290
[Wu Yeol is pacing around for a while]

234
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:20,850
[And the bell rings]

235
00:15:32,920 --> 00:15:34,260
- Hey.
- Yu Gyeong.

236
00:15:34,260 --> 00:15:36,530
- Did you go on a date with Seong Min?
- Yes.

237
00:15:36,530 --> 00:15:37,960
- Seong Min?
- Yes.

238
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:40,700
- Everyone is busy.
- Right.

239
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:43,430
- Should I get busy, too?
- So cute.

240
00:15:43,430 --> 00:15:46,300
Why should only men initiate dates?

241
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:47,540
Right, you should.

242
00:15:47,540 --> 00:15:49,590
Who should I ask out?

243
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:54,700
- I don't know. This is too hard.
- It really is.

244
00:15:54,700 --> 00:15:57,430
I really have no idea.

245
00:15:57,430 --> 00:15:58,490
It's complicated.

246
00:15:58,490 --> 00:16:01,210
Is no one going to drink?

247
00:16:01,210 --> 00:16:04,120
- I can't.
- We get to sleep in tomorrow, Unni.

248
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:07,550
Stop it. I can't keep my eyes open.

249
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:11,390
I'm happy. I'm having a dopamine rush.

250
00:16:11,390 --> 00:16:13,360
Because I can sleep in tomorrow.

251
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:14,750
She must be bothered by her.

252
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:16,560
I'm happy.

253
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:20,060
Did you go hard tonight, Unni?

254
00:16:20,060 --> 00:16:23,250
I don't ever drink whiskey.

255
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:26,490
But I decided to give it a try.

256
00:16:26,490 --> 00:16:29,740
I realized it's not for me.

257
00:16:29,740 --> 00:16:32,680
- It's no good.
- Look at Yu Gyeong's face.

258
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:36,090
- How come?
- Wu Yeol was like,

259
00:16:36,090 --> 00:16:38,000
"You're hurting my pride."

260
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:41,800
He was a little drunk,
but I wasn't drunk at all.

261
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:46,000
His ego was bruised,
and we had a drinking competition.

262
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,190
I didn't get drunk.

263
00:16:49,630 --> 00:16:51,310
I'll be better.

264
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:55,180
Why am I so sad?

265
00:16:59,880 --> 00:17:00,990
Where are you going?

266
00:17:00,990 --> 00:17:03,260
I'm going downstairs.

267
00:17:06,100 --> 00:17:07,760
So, what did you do today?

268
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:10,470
- I hung out with Seong Min.
- Since when?

269
00:17:10,470 --> 00:17:13,050
We had dinner and came home right away.

270
00:17:13,050 --> 00:17:17,480
I don't know how people come home
after midnight.

271
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:19,580
All we did was eat.

272
00:17:20,330 --> 00:17:22,270
We came home so early.

273
00:17:22,270 --> 00:17:24,230
I feel so small.

274
00:17:25,260 --> 00:17:27,960
You went on many dates with Wu Yeol.

275
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:29,550
But...

276
00:17:31,430 --> 00:17:33,640
- You're right.
- You went out with everyone but me.

277
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:36,700
That's right. Everyone but you.

278
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:38,170
Will we ever go out?

279
00:17:38,170 --> 00:17:40,070
You hate me, don't you?

280
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:43,680
You aren't interested in me.

281
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:44,980
The ideal type is...

282
00:17:44,980 --> 00:17:47,340
[Jun Hyeon is entering the living room]

283
00:17:47,340 --> 00:17:50,560
- Jun Hyeon is here.
- I love that we can talk about work.

284
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:52,640
Really?

285
00:17:53,210 --> 00:17:55,140
[And Wu Yeol]

286
00:17:55,140 --> 00:17:57,930
Wu Yeol is coming downstairs.

287
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:02,880
[Everyone is discussing their view on love]

288
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:03,900
[Glancing]

289
00:18:03,900 --> 00:18:08,020
I forget about everything but good memories.

290
00:18:08,020 --> 00:18:11,050
- It must have its downsides.
- There he goes.

291
00:18:11,050 --> 00:18:13,030
It's important where Wu Yeol sits.

292
00:18:13,030 --> 00:18:18,060
Sounds like you can think logically
even after falling in love.

293
00:18:18,060 --> 00:18:20,300
You could be interested in someone,

294
00:18:20,300 --> 00:18:23,790
but dating needs to be more serious.

295
00:18:23,790 --> 00:18:25,760
- I think you have to learn
- So cautious.

296
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:28,590
about each other first before you date.

297
00:18:28,590 --> 00:18:31,210
Relationships take more than just interests.

298
00:18:31,210 --> 00:18:35,200
You really have to like each other
to be in a relationship.

299
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:36,870
That's how I am.

300
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:41,030
She has a lot to think about.

301
00:18:43,220 --> 00:18:44,530
[Glancing]

302
00:18:47,190 --> 00:18:50,070
[Seo Won is going upstairs]

303
00:18:50,070 --> 00:18:52,840
Do you want this? A chocolate churro?

304
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,010
Sounds good.

305
00:18:54,630 --> 00:18:56,030
Thanks.

306
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:58,130
Is it just one?

307
00:18:58,130 --> 00:18:59,750
- Do you want to split it?
- Split it.

308
00:18:59,750 --> 00:19:00,990
Have half. It's sweet.

309
00:19:00,990 --> 00:19:03,010
- He cares for her.
- Take the first bite.

310
00:19:03,010 --> 00:19:04,980
I'll have the rest.

311
00:19:08,530 --> 00:19:12,110
So? Is that all you did today?

312
00:19:12,880 --> 00:19:15,830
Yes, we just had dinner.

313
00:19:15,830 --> 00:19:17,650
Alone?

314
00:19:17,650 --> 00:19:19,760
Oh, with Seong Min?

315
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:23,890
[Dropping crumbs]

316
00:19:27,820 --> 00:19:29,280
Thanks.

317
00:19:33,470 --> 00:19:38,060
[Frustration won't fade easily]

318
00:19:38,780 --> 00:19:40,490
[Sigh]

319
00:19:41,490 --> 00:19:43,220
Gosh.

320
00:20:04,670 --> 00:20:07,110
[A relaxing weekend morning]

321
00:20:09,790 --> 00:20:14,450
[Wu Yeol is starting his day early]

322
00:20:14,450 --> 00:20:16,520
Is he leaving early?

323
00:20:25,180 --> 00:20:30,340
[Seong Min is starting his day, too]

324
00:20:34,750 --> 00:20:36,500
[Moist]

325
00:20:41,330 --> 00:20:43,330
What are you doing, Hyung?

326
00:20:43,330 --> 00:20:45,960
I'm putting on what I usually wear.

327
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:48,130
I just need to wear this and
sunscreen. It's so easy.

328
00:20:48,130 --> 00:20:49,820
How nice.

329
00:20:54,890 --> 00:20:56,510
Nice, huh?

330
00:20:57,360 --> 00:20:59,460
Put it all over your face.

331
00:21:00,180 --> 00:21:01,450
Like this?

332
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:04,100
It's moist.

333
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:06,740
I can totally trust you on this.

334
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:09,010
- Do you want it?
- Yes.

335
00:21:09,010 --> 00:21:10,540
So nice.

336
00:21:11,320 --> 00:21:13,640
This is new for these two.

337
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:16,700
- I'm thinking of cooking.
- Me, too.

338
00:21:16,700 --> 00:21:19,510
- Really? Want to join me?
- Yes, I think I should do something.

339
00:21:19,510 --> 00:21:20,820
How's galbijjim?

340
00:21:20,820 --> 00:21:23,240
- Do we have the ingredients?
- No, I'm thinking of getting them.

341
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:25,860
Oh, you want to go grocery shopping?

342
00:21:25,860 --> 00:21:27,940
- Gochujang stew?
- Sounds good.

343
00:21:27,940 --> 00:21:30,410
- We have tofu and everything.
- That's a good idea.

344
00:21:30,410 --> 00:21:33,620
Gochujang stew and galbijjim?

345
00:21:33,620 --> 00:21:36,250
She's cooking. I've never seen her cooking.

346
00:21:40,390 --> 00:21:44,020
I think I'll put the entire bottle
of this sauce.

347
00:21:44,020 --> 00:21:46,400
- Did you sleep well?
- Min Ju is here.

348
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:50,100
I'm the last person to wake up.
Wow, what's this?

349
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:51,950
- Did you make all this, Oppa?
- No.

350
00:21:51,950 --> 00:21:53,360
- Gyu Ri did.
- We made it together.

351
00:21:53,360 --> 00:21:55,110
Unni.

352
00:21:59,900 --> 00:22:04,150
Galbijjim was Wu Yeol's request.

353
00:22:04,150 --> 00:22:05,340
Really?

354
00:22:05,340 --> 00:22:09,150
- That's why she made it.
- That must be.

355
00:22:10,150 --> 00:22:11,930
Really?

356
00:22:11,930 --> 00:22:16,350
I've been talking about making galbijjim.

357
00:22:16,350 --> 00:22:20,490
Remember? I wanted to make it from Day 1.

358
00:22:20,490 --> 00:22:24,260
She's upset that she cooked with Seong Min.

359
00:22:24,260 --> 00:22:27,510
- Looks amazing.
- It's perfect.

360
00:22:28,340 --> 00:22:30,240
Daebak.

361
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:33,180
Is it good?

362
00:22:33,180 --> 00:22:34,730
It's good.

363
00:22:38,900 --> 00:22:40,290
Good morning.

364
00:22:40,290 --> 00:22:42,040
- What?
- Did you eat?

365
00:22:42,040 --> 00:22:44,380
So Yun is into Seo Won now.

366
00:22:45,420 --> 00:22:47,060
It's melting.

367
00:22:47,060 --> 00:22:49,060
You did an amazing job.

368
00:22:49,990 --> 00:22:52,180
Wow, thank you.

369
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:58,700
Nothing is ever easy for So Yun.

370
00:22:58,700 --> 00:23:00,460
What are you doing today, Min Ju?

371
00:23:00,460 --> 00:23:02,270
I haven't decided yet.

372
00:23:02,270 --> 00:23:03,880
Wu Yeol isn't here yet.

373
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:06,150
I saw him going out.

374
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:11,290
Do we not know
what time Wu Yeol is coming back?

375
00:23:11,290 --> 00:23:12,800
We don't.

376
00:23:17,630 --> 00:23:20,030
Bowling sounds fun, too.

377
00:23:20,030 --> 00:23:22,760
Want to go bowling? I love bowling.

378
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:24,890
Can you leave right away?

379
00:23:24,890 --> 00:23:27,050
- Should we get ready?
- Let's get ready.

380
00:23:28,160 --> 00:23:30,800
[So Yun is getting ready to go out]

381
00:23:45,910 --> 00:23:48,460
So Yun, are you all ready?

382
00:23:48,460 --> 00:23:51,070
I'm covering my dark circles.

383
00:23:52,060 --> 00:23:54,240
You look so fresh.

384
00:23:55,210 --> 00:23:56,680
Will you take it with you?

385
00:23:56,680 --> 00:23:58,160
Yes.

386
00:23:58,160 --> 00:24:01,320
[A relaxing weekend afternoon]

387
00:24:02,430 --> 00:24:05,740
Seo Won, Seong Min, Gyu Ri, and So Yun.

388
00:24:05,740 --> 00:24:07,390
- They said they're going somewhere.
- Bowling.

389
00:24:07,390 --> 00:24:10,160
- Bowling?
- I'm nervous.

390
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,850
Bowling sounds fun, too.

391
00:24:11,850 --> 00:24:13,450
Want to go bowling? I love bowling.

392
00:24:13,450 --> 00:24:15,050
I feel like being active today.

393
00:24:15,050 --> 00:24:18,620
- Let's not come home tonight.
- Let's come home at 4:00 a.m.

394
00:24:18,620 --> 00:24:19,970
Hold on. Who's sitting in the front?

395
00:24:19,970 --> 00:24:21,340
That's important.

396
00:24:22,070 --> 00:24:23,620
Can I sit in the front?

397
00:24:24,390 --> 00:24:25,400
[Glancing]

398
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:27,100
Let's go.

399
00:24:27,100 --> 00:24:29,230
Let's put the seatbelts on.

400
00:24:30,020 --> 00:24:31,620
Put the seatbelt on.

401
00:24:31,620 --> 00:24:33,660
So Yun must be a little sad.

402
00:24:33,660 --> 00:24:35,950
- Are you tight back there?
- There's plenty of space.

403
00:24:35,950 --> 00:24:39,130
No one knows that So Yun
has feelings for Seo Won.

404
00:24:39,130 --> 00:24:40,830
I know.

405
00:24:40,830 --> 00:24:42,630
- Everyone is buckled up, right?
- Yes.

406
00:24:42,630 --> 00:24:44,290
Good job.

407
00:24:44,890 --> 00:24:45,770
[Glancing]

408
00:24:49,310 --> 00:24:50,600
[Rolling down]

409
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:53,260
Did he roll down the window for her?

410
00:24:58,130 --> 00:25:00,470
- So Yun is...
- I feel bad for So Yun.

411
00:25:00,470 --> 00:25:02,750
I know. She joined late.

412
00:25:02,750 --> 00:25:04,980
A lot happened in a week.

413
00:25:04,980 --> 00:25:07,110
[Looking at Seo Won, feeling conflicted]

414
00:25:11,290 --> 00:25:13,690
Are we forming teams like this?

415
00:25:13,690 --> 00:25:15,060
No, that's no good.

416
00:25:15,060 --> 00:25:16,500
Would that be okay?

417
00:25:16,500 --> 00:25:17,800
Sure.

418
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:19,320
Okay.

419
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:22,260
Have you done a spare?

420
00:25:22,260 --> 00:25:25,220
- Impressive, right?
- What's a spare?

421
00:25:25,220 --> 00:25:26,790
We can do it.

422
00:25:26,790 --> 00:25:29,500
Let's go! Let's go.

423
00:25:29,500 --> 00:25:32,590
I think I've gotten a lot of strikes.

424
00:25:33,610 --> 00:25:36,010
[So Yun, trying to intimidate in advance]

425
00:25:36,010 --> 00:25:38,240
- I love a competition.
- Let's go.

426
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:39,610
- We need to win.
- We need to.

427
00:25:39,610 --> 00:25:42,560
I wrote a note saying not to do the dishes.

428
00:25:42,560 --> 00:25:44,670
The losers are doing the dishes.

429
00:25:46,420 --> 00:25:51,540
[Entering the bowling alley]

430
00:25:51,540 --> 00:25:56,020
[A satisfying strike]

431
00:25:56,020 --> 00:25:58,610
[Can they make a way in their
frustrating relationships, too?]

432
00:25:58,610 --> 00:26:00,160
- It's so nice.
- What's your size?

433
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:01,930
- 40.
- You should wear 35, then.

434
00:26:01,930 --> 00:26:03,690
35 is over there.

435
00:26:03,690 --> 00:26:05,990
He's so caring.

436
00:26:07,180 --> 00:26:08,410
Size 75.

437
00:26:08,410 --> 00:26:11,330
- Let's bring them over.
- Let's put them on there.

438
00:26:11,330 --> 00:26:13,430
[Laughing]

439
00:26:14,490 --> 00:26:16,030
Put them on both and walk.

440
00:26:16,030 --> 00:26:20,360
[Took the shoes off too eagerly]

441
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:25,410
- You sure are hasty.
- Thank you.

442
00:26:25,410 --> 00:26:26,480
[You little]

443
00:26:27,260 --> 00:26:30,410
Lanes five and six.

444
00:26:31,560 --> 00:26:32,840
[So Yun is sitting next to Seo Won]

445
00:26:32,840 --> 00:26:34,860
She's sitting next to him.

446
00:26:34,860 --> 00:26:36,300
Nice.

447
00:26:42,260 --> 00:26:45,210
[Seo Won is picking a ball for Gyu Ri]

448
00:26:45,210 --> 00:26:46,800
Do it like this.

449
00:26:47,750 --> 00:26:50,560
- One by one?
- One by one? Sounds good.

450
00:26:52,090 --> 00:26:52,940
[Looking]

451
00:26:52,940 --> 00:26:54,690
It must bother her.

452
00:26:54,690 --> 00:26:58,110
[She can't stop looking at them]

453
00:26:58,110 --> 00:26:59,400
Good.

454
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:02,650
Teach me, too.

455
00:27:06,900 --> 00:27:09,590
- Should we come up with team names first?
- Sounds good.

456
00:27:09,590 --> 00:27:10,880
What should we name our team?

457
00:27:10,880 --> 00:27:12,910
What about Team Minsomae*?
(Means "sleeveless")

458
00:27:12,910 --> 00:27:14,070
I like it.

459
00:27:14,070 --> 00:27:16,080
- Minsomae.
- Seong Min, So Yun.

460
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:19,940
[Formed Team Minsomae]

461
00:27:19,940 --> 00:27:21,000
- Gyu Ri.
- Seo Won.

462
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:22,920
- Fighting!
- Fighting!

463
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:24,310
- Too old-fashioned.
- Too old-fashioned.

464
00:27:24,310 --> 00:27:26,700
[Dissing each other harshly]

465
00:27:26,700 --> 00:27:30,530
I'll start, then.
Going first is nerve-racking.

466
00:27:30,530 --> 00:27:32,020
No tackling.

467
00:27:32,020 --> 00:27:34,360
- I'll go.
- Okay.

468
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:36,600
[Goofing]

469
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:38,880
Wow, a nice throw.

470
00:27:40,490 --> 00:27:42,160
- He's good.
- Not bad.

471
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:44,600
He's good. Seo Won is good.

472
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:46,100
Wow!

473
00:27:46,100 --> 00:27:47,990
- Nice, nice.
- He's experienced.

474
00:27:47,990 --> 00:27:51,240
- A strike. So dramatic.
- Seo Won is cool.

475
00:27:51,970 --> 00:27:54,870
I got a good teammate.

476
00:27:56,140 --> 00:27:58,940
[Seong Min's turn]

477
00:27:58,940 --> 00:28:01,730
[His ball veered off]

478
00:28:01,730 --> 00:28:03,880
- That was so close.
- They're good.

479
00:28:03,880 --> 00:28:05,680
They're good.

480
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:08,100
Gyu Ri's turn. Go, Noona.

481
00:28:09,930 --> 00:28:12,080
Bowling is all about the rhythm.

482
00:28:13,080 --> 00:28:17,380
Bend your knees and roll quietly from here.

483
00:28:17,380 --> 00:28:18,830
Okay.

484
00:28:18,830 --> 00:28:21,690
We're done. We're done. We're winners.

485
00:28:21,690 --> 00:28:24,250
- What's the prize again?
- Can I throw mine here?

486
00:28:24,250 --> 00:28:26,320
It's over, Noona.

487
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:29,140
Slightly to the right.
Since you're on the left.

488
00:28:29,140 --> 00:28:31,230
- It feels crooked.
- No, it's okay.

489
00:28:31,230 --> 00:28:33,280
Stuff like this is too much.

490
00:28:34,550 --> 00:28:35,640
Okay, okay.

491
00:28:35,640 --> 00:28:37,480
- It slipped out of my fingers.
- I know, good job.

492
00:28:37,480 --> 00:28:39,490
- My fingers hurt.
- Do you want the tape?

493
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:44,190
[Seo Won is putting the tape on her]

494
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:50,190
[Tossing again without hesitation]

495
00:28:50,190 --> 00:28:52,760
He's done it a lot before. Oh, yeah.

496
00:28:52,760 --> 00:28:55,060
[Two strikes in a row]

497
00:28:55,060 --> 00:28:58,050
We are the winners.

498
00:28:58,050 --> 00:29:01,590
[As time passes,
it's getting more noticeable]

499
00:29:01,590 --> 00:29:04,820
[how affectionate they are]

500
00:29:04,820 --> 00:29:07,120
I like challenges.

501
00:29:09,270 --> 00:29:13,200
When I saw Gyu Ri and Seo Won
side by side like that,

502
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:19,700
I thought Gyu Ri definitely had
feelings for Seo Won, but...

503
00:29:20,790 --> 00:29:22,890
I saw the two on the sofa in the living room.

504
00:29:22,890 --> 00:29:26,190
She sensed something then. She knows.

505
00:29:27,100 --> 00:29:28,790
- What?
- I'll be upstairs.

506
00:29:28,790 --> 00:29:30,760
No, no. Why?

507
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:34,120
- So Yun seems to know what's going on.
- She does because she's clever.

508
00:29:34,120 --> 00:29:35,820
Who wants soju?

509
00:29:35,820 --> 00:29:38,150
You're so determined today.

510
00:29:38,150 --> 00:29:39,960
Of course, she feels that way.

511
00:29:39,960 --> 00:29:43,500
I thought of that as an opportunity.

512
00:29:43,500 --> 00:29:46,760
- Right, right. That's right.
- It's visible to So Yun.

513
00:29:46,760 --> 00:29:49,650
Why did Gyu Ri have to tag along?

514
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:53,770
[Approaching]

515
00:29:53,770 --> 00:29:55,320
[So Yun is on Seo Won's side]

516
00:29:55,320 --> 00:29:58,070
I hit nine all the time.

517
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:02,990
Nice. Seo Won is good.

518
00:30:02,990 --> 00:30:04,110
[Seo Won scores a strike]

519
00:30:04,110 --> 00:30:07,000
- Another strike?
- He's very good.

520
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:08,100
[High five]

521
00:30:08,100 --> 00:30:09,210
She's so cute.

522
00:30:09,210 --> 00:30:12,680
[Successfully high-fived]

523
00:30:12,680 --> 00:30:14,100
It's not going to the center.

524
00:30:14,100 --> 00:30:17,570
[Seong Min scored]

525
00:30:18,250 --> 00:30:21,100
[Stealing the high five]

526
00:30:22,640 --> 00:30:23,430
[High five]

527
00:30:26,970 --> 00:30:29,210
[She is making opportunities]

528
00:30:29,210 --> 00:30:31,980
- Good job.
- She keeps looking for opportunities.

529
00:30:31,980 --> 00:30:35,350
- She's not an easy opponent.
- Of course not.

530
00:30:35,350 --> 00:30:38,680
Right. She shouldn't be tolerating this.

531
00:30:38,680 --> 00:30:42,560
[The game is coming to an end]

532
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:44,630
We're the same.

533
00:30:44,630 --> 00:30:47,490
I know. It's 116-115-53-50.

534
00:30:47,490 --> 00:30:50,450
[The scores are neck and neck]

535
00:30:50,450 --> 00:30:52,510
We are only two points apart.

536
00:30:52,510 --> 00:30:55,610
- It's been between the two.
- I know, it's a duel.

537
00:30:55,610 --> 00:30:57,770
A game of a lifetime.

538
00:30:57,770 --> 00:30:59,670
Nice, nice, nice.

539
00:30:59,670 --> 00:31:01,500
[Succeeded 1 out of 10]

540
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:03,290
Okay, okay. It's okay.

541
00:31:03,290 --> 00:31:06,540
[It's So Yun's game to win]

542
00:31:06,540 --> 00:31:08,560
Good luck.

543
00:31:08,560 --> 00:31:09,880
Look at Seong Min. Look at Seong Min.

544
00:31:09,880 --> 00:31:11,450
You're stepping on the line.

545
00:31:12,160 --> 00:31:15,080
Seong Min only cares about winning right now.

546
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:18,380
[What will So Yun do?]

547
00:31:18,380 --> 00:31:20,620
It's over once it goes to the center.

548
00:31:20,620 --> 00:31:22,430
No!

549
00:31:22,430 --> 00:31:24,770
[Into the gutter]

550
00:31:24,770 --> 00:31:27,420
- I'm sorry.
- How could this happen?

551
00:31:27,420 --> 00:31:29,160
- I'm sorry.
- No, no, no.

552
00:31:29,160 --> 00:31:32,530
We are doing the dishes, then.

553
00:31:32,530 --> 00:31:34,140
[It's already the last round]

554
00:31:34,140 --> 00:31:36,260
- Want to try switching team members?
- That's right!

555
00:31:36,260 --> 00:31:39,510
- Wow, good job.
- We're picking up alcohol later.

556
00:31:39,510 --> 00:31:41,460
Should we switch
and make the losers pay for it?

557
00:31:41,460 --> 00:31:43,700
- This is the real round.
- It is. We can do the dishes.

558
00:31:43,700 --> 00:31:44,850
We're in your care.

559
00:31:44,850 --> 00:31:45,990
Should we play here?

560
00:31:45,990 --> 00:31:47,660
That's a long handshake.

561
00:31:48,570 --> 00:31:50,250
I'll coach you one more time.

562
00:31:50,250 --> 00:31:52,130
Nice, nice.

563
00:31:52,130 --> 00:31:53,990
I lost my coach.

564
00:31:53,990 --> 00:31:56,680
- I want to play this round seriously.
- I'm serious, too.

565
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:58,770
Were you not serious before?

566
00:31:58,770 --> 00:32:00,370
Of course, I was.

567
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:06,530
Great! That's a good one.

568
00:32:06,530 --> 00:32:08,010
Just one. Just one. It's okay.

569
00:32:08,010 --> 00:32:10,360
No, I'll score a strike next time.

570
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:12,250
That's what we've been doing.

571
00:32:12,250 --> 00:32:14,260
[Doing a high five behind her back]

572
00:32:14,260 --> 00:32:17,470
So Yun's face changed. She's so happy.

573
00:32:17,470 --> 00:32:19,540
Gyu Ri's face changed, too.

574
00:32:19,540 --> 00:32:20,760
Don't feel pressured now.

575
00:32:20,760 --> 00:32:22,600
Pretend like you're at home.

576
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:25,200
You're walking around your house.

577
00:32:25,850 --> 00:32:27,540
You're tossing a ball at your dog.

578
00:32:27,540 --> 00:32:29,050
Sorry.

579
00:32:30,530 --> 00:32:32,230
I like the taking-a-walk vibe.

580
00:32:32,230 --> 00:32:34,810
[What's the result of his training?]

581
00:32:34,810 --> 00:32:36,660
[A huge success]

582
00:32:38,050 --> 00:32:40,930
- Nice. Turn right.
- Please, please.

583
00:32:40,930 --> 00:32:43,320
- Nice.
- Wow, what?

584
00:32:43,320 --> 00:32:46,170
[She suddenly improved]

585
00:32:46,170 --> 00:32:48,100
You're amazing.

586
00:32:48,100 --> 00:32:49,540
We did it. We did it.

587
00:32:49,540 --> 00:32:51,670
How does it spin like that?

588
00:32:51,670 --> 00:32:53,420
[She finally scored a strike]

589
00:32:53,420 --> 00:32:56,170
- Wow, So Yun.
- Daebak, daebak.

590
00:32:56,870 --> 00:32:58,080
She's good.

591
00:32:58,900 --> 00:33:03,610
Nice. Why weren't you doing that before?

592
00:33:03,610 --> 00:33:06,250
- I want someone else to pay for my drink.
- Right.

593
00:33:06,250 --> 00:33:08,030
It tastes better that way.

594
00:33:08,030 --> 00:33:10,450
If he can't get that...

595
00:33:10,450 --> 00:33:13,950
- we'll be in a good mood.
- No. No way.

596
00:33:13,950 --> 00:33:16,230
Let's always root for them.

597
00:33:17,550 --> 00:33:20,430
- No sighing allowed.
- Of course.

598
00:33:20,430 --> 00:33:22,070
[Trying to sabotage]

599
00:33:22,070 --> 00:33:24,130
Don't you have to sneeze?

600
00:33:25,100 --> 00:33:26,310
They're both cute.

601
00:33:26,310 --> 00:33:29,470
- It's okay. It's okay. It's nice.
- Don't cry.

602
00:33:29,470 --> 00:33:32,450
- I can do it. Since I get strikes...
- Fighting.

603
00:33:32,450 --> 00:33:33,960
Fighting.

604
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:37,050
- I'll go for a walk.
- So Yun must be falling for Seo Won.

605
00:33:37,050 --> 00:33:38,610
Take a walk in the house.

606
00:33:38,610 --> 00:33:41,390
- Roll the ball to your dog.
- It feels stuffy here.

607
00:33:41,390 --> 00:33:43,150
Puppy.

608
00:33:43,150 --> 00:33:46,200
[What's the puppy's response?]

609
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:49,320
[A satisfying strike]

610
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:51,730
- Just trust me.
- I always have.

611
00:33:51,730 --> 00:33:53,620
I just need to score a strike.

612
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:56,590
- I got it. I got it.
- Here we go.

613
00:33:56,590 --> 00:33:58,070
[Failed to strike, unfortunately]

614
00:33:58,070 --> 00:34:01,670
[Teasing in perfect harmony]

615
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:05,880
Let's just keep at it.

616
00:34:05,880 --> 00:34:06,530
[We're the best]

617
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:08,260
[The best]

618
00:34:08,260 --> 00:34:09,900
Nice.

619
00:34:14,070 --> 00:34:16,280
Don't feel pressured.

620
00:34:16,280 --> 00:34:19,150
You pressured him just now.

621
00:34:19,150 --> 00:34:20,290
[Into the gutter]

622
00:34:20,290 --> 00:34:22,470
She just pressured you.

623
00:34:26,170 --> 00:34:28,380
- It's my fault that we lost.
- No, no.

624
00:34:28,380 --> 00:34:30,520
I wanted to buy you drinks.

625
00:34:30,520 --> 00:34:32,010
- Nice.
- So Yun is happy.

626
00:34:32,010 --> 00:34:35,360
We lost in the end because of me. I'm sorry.

627
00:34:35,360 --> 00:34:37,810
I'll write this in my diary
and reflect on it.

628
00:34:38,590 --> 00:34:39,380
I'm dizzy.

629
00:34:39,380 --> 00:34:42,610
Isn't this the most complicated
Heart Signal yet?

630
00:34:42,610 --> 00:34:44,940
- It is. I'm confused.
- With connections...

631
00:34:44,940 --> 00:34:46,420
and love triangles...

632
00:34:46,420 --> 00:34:50,350
From what I saw in the bowling alley,
So Yun likes him a lot more than I thought.

633
00:34:50,350 --> 00:34:53,380
It's a good thing
she suggested switching teams.

634
00:34:53,380 --> 00:34:55,230
She found the perfect timing.

635
00:34:55,940 --> 00:34:58,260
[A sunny afternoon, Itaewon-ro]

636
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:00,580
[Jun Hyeon is waiting for his nickname date]

637
00:35:00,580 --> 00:35:04,400
He's the closest thing
to my type this season.

638
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:08,640
[Nervous]

639
00:35:13,690 --> 00:35:15,090
Who is it?

640
00:35:15,710 --> 00:35:18,610
[Jun Hyeon chose...]

641
00:35:18,610 --> 00:35:20,320
Yu Gyeong. It's Yu Gyeong.

642
00:35:21,210 --> 00:35:22,540
[Spotted him]

643
00:35:24,750 --> 00:35:26,570
Oppa.

644
00:35:26,570 --> 00:35:28,830
[Happy to see her]

645
00:35:28,830 --> 00:35:31,200
What? Did you walk?

646
00:35:31,200 --> 00:35:35,300
- Did you walk here?
- Yes, I did.

647
00:35:35,300 --> 00:35:37,610
- Did you wait a long time?
- I did.

648
00:35:37,610 --> 00:35:39,900
- I waited forever.
- Really?

649
00:35:40,650 --> 00:35:43,080
Did you expect to see me?

650
00:35:43,080 --> 00:35:44,510
I didn't.

651
00:35:44,510 --> 00:35:47,300
- I didn't have any information.
- Really?

652
00:35:47,300 --> 00:35:49,900
I'm here to meet Beluga today.

653
00:35:49,900 --> 00:35:51,710
I'm Beluga.

654
00:35:53,410 --> 00:35:55,540
You're Beluga of the Forest?

655
00:35:55,540 --> 00:35:57,200
Are you Yellow?

656
00:35:59,880 --> 00:36:01,690
- Are you?
- Who knows?

657
00:36:01,690 --> 00:36:04,330
- I think you're Yellow.
- Really?

658
00:36:04,330 --> 00:36:07,010
- He can't look at her.
- Maybe you'll see her in the evening.

659
00:36:07,010 --> 00:36:08,970
Will I?

660
00:36:08,970 --> 00:36:11,950
- I like these two, too.
- Thank you.

661
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:14,320
[Pop]

662
00:36:15,950 --> 00:36:17,700
It's so puffy.

663
00:36:18,460 --> 00:36:21,360
Looks delicious.

664
00:36:25,350 --> 00:36:28,850
It kind of tastes like a taco.

665
00:36:28,850 --> 00:36:30,590
You're right

666
00:36:31,630 --> 00:36:34,050
- Do you like tacos?
- I do.

667
00:36:34,050 --> 00:36:36,550
Really? You're copying me.

668
00:36:36,550 --> 00:36:38,730
I absolutely love them.

669
00:36:39,700 --> 00:36:42,060
I used to be addicted to tacos.

670
00:36:42,060 --> 00:36:44,660
I used to travel to try tacos.

671
00:36:44,660 --> 00:36:47,880
We had a lot of similarities.

672
00:36:47,880 --> 00:36:49,400
- A.
- It's A.

673
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:55,000
[Jun Hyeon is always a half beat late]

674
00:36:55,540 --> 00:36:59,840
I was wondering
if you were copying my answers.

675
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:02,790
- What do you think of me?
- She's seeing through you.

676
00:37:02,790 --> 00:37:04,810
You're right about everything.

677
00:37:04,810 --> 00:37:07,110
- Yes.
- I'm kidding. I really am.

678
00:37:07,110 --> 00:37:09,490
- You actually agreed with me?
- Yes.

679
00:37:09,490 --> 00:37:11,580
- You really thought that?
- Right.

680
00:37:11,580 --> 00:37:12,680
I was being sincere.

681
00:37:12,680 --> 00:37:16,180
- I always love watching these two.
- Love their banter.

682
00:37:16,180 --> 00:37:18,740
Do you listen to ballads?

683
00:37:18,740 --> 00:37:20,490
I do a lot.

684
00:37:20,490 --> 00:37:23,010
I like Roy Kim and Paul Kim.

685
00:37:23,650 --> 00:37:28,720
[Suddenly getting recognition]

686
00:37:28,720 --> 00:37:30,910
- All of a sudden.
- Let's get it.

687
00:37:30,910 --> 00:37:33,590
- Roy, Roy, Roy.
- I get her taste.

688
00:37:33,590 --> 00:37:35,840
I like Roy Kim and Paul Kim.

689
00:37:35,840 --> 00:37:38,590
You don't like the intense kind.

690
00:37:38,590 --> 00:37:42,510
- Not the intense ballad.
- Yes, I like the gentle kind.

691
00:37:43,510 --> 00:37:46,500
I've been to a Paul Kim concert.

692
00:37:46,500 --> 00:37:48,970
- She's only been to Paul Kim's.
- Not Roy Kim's.

693
00:37:48,970 --> 00:37:50,550
[My goodness]

694
00:37:50,550 --> 00:37:52,700
It was probably sold out.

695
00:37:52,700 --> 00:37:54,400
Is that the latest one you've been to?

696
00:37:54,400 --> 00:37:56,470
No, that was a while ago.

697
00:37:56,470 --> 00:37:59,170
I've been to musicals mostly.

698
00:37:59,170 --> 00:38:02,020
- Because she does the musical.
- Musicals?

699
00:38:02,770 --> 00:38:06,580
I'm sad because nobody here
is interested in musicals.

700
00:38:06,580 --> 00:38:09,450
- I'm interested in musicals. Really.
- Stop lying.

701
00:38:09,450 --> 00:38:11,490
I've been to a musical recently.

702
00:38:11,490 --> 00:38:12,840
- Which one?
- Moulin Rouge.

703
00:38:12,840 --> 00:38:14,400
Really?

704
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:16,570
Why? I'm serious.

705
00:38:16,570 --> 00:38:20,200
I have that thing, too. Binoculars.

706
00:38:20,200 --> 00:38:22,300
- Right.
- Musicals are always fun.

707
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:24,452
It's always guaranteed that you'll have fun.

708
00:38:24,452 --> 00:38:25,875
Right?

709
00:38:25,875 --> 00:38:27,585
That's why I like it.

710
00:38:28,240 --> 00:38:32,110
I heard you've been in a musical.

711
00:38:32,110 --> 00:38:36,430
People didn't show reactions
when I mentioned it.

712
00:38:36,430 --> 00:38:39,260
I feel awkward bringing it up at first.

713
00:38:39,260 --> 00:38:42,810
I can't be like,
"You know, I actually like musicals."

714
00:38:42,810 --> 00:38:45,760
- He can never do that.
- I guess I can say...

715
00:38:46,430 --> 00:38:48,530
I'm not used to being like that.

716
00:38:48,530 --> 00:38:51,380
Do you rarely talk about yourself?

717
00:38:56,840 --> 00:39:01,960
I'm actually not like that
with people I'm close to.

718
00:39:01,960 --> 00:39:05,860
I tend to share everything I do every day.

719
00:39:05,860 --> 00:39:07,600
You share what you did each day?

720
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:09,630
I send photos a lot, too.

721
00:39:09,630 --> 00:39:12,120
Really? If you're close to the person?

722
00:39:12,120 --> 00:39:14,490
- Interesting.
- He'd be cute in a relationship.

723
00:39:14,490 --> 00:39:16,340
Do you have to say good morning, too?

724
00:39:16,340 --> 00:39:18,360
Good morning? That's a must.

725
00:39:20,300 --> 00:39:25,910
But I get sad when they're like,
"I'm going out now" after getting all ready.

726
00:39:26,660 --> 00:39:29,540
You have to text "Good morning"
and a heart symbol first thing.

727
00:39:29,540 --> 00:39:31,380
Really?

728
00:39:32,830 --> 00:39:35,190
I do it because I want to.

729
00:39:35,190 --> 00:39:37,720
- He's so charming.
- He really is.

730
00:39:37,720 --> 00:39:39,160
Right, right.

731
00:39:40,360 --> 00:39:43,860
I noticed that your eyes are so...

732
00:39:43,860 --> 00:39:45,350
- My eyes?
- "My eyes?"

733
00:39:45,350 --> 00:39:47,890
Whose eyes, then?

734
00:39:47,890 --> 00:39:50,360
- They're puffy.
- Should I say they're clear?

735
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:54,840
Your pupils are pretty.

736
00:39:54,840 --> 00:40:01,000
It's because I have a healthy mindset
and a pure personality.

737
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:03,060
- He's the funniest when they're together.
- Are you pure?

738
00:40:03,060 --> 00:40:05,850
Of course, I am. Can't you tell?

739
00:40:05,850 --> 00:40:07,530
Slightly muddy.

740
00:40:08,940 --> 00:40:11,370
They are semi-transparent.

741
00:40:11,370 --> 00:40:13,600
Thank you.

742
00:40:13,600 --> 00:40:15,660
So cute.

743
00:40:15,660 --> 00:40:17,860
- So cute.
- What?

744
00:40:21,180 --> 00:40:23,500
I like this.

745
00:40:23,500 --> 00:40:25,130
These flavors?

746
00:40:26,890 --> 00:40:29,990
I haven't had brunch outside in a while.

747
00:40:29,990 --> 00:40:31,940
It's a special occasion.

748
00:40:32,790 --> 00:40:34,280
It is.

749
00:40:35,690 --> 00:40:37,420
It is a special occasion.

750
00:40:37,420 --> 00:40:41,400
- I love how he says that casually.
- The weather is nice. It's warm.

751
00:40:42,570 --> 00:40:44,380
[Taking a walk in front
of a theater for Yu Gyeong]

752
00:40:44,380 --> 00:40:47,000
- "Arang"?
- Yes, that's it.

753
00:40:47,000 --> 00:40:48,780
"Arang"?

754
00:40:48,780 --> 00:40:50,890
This place is nice.

755
00:40:51,480 --> 00:40:53,790
You did "The Last Empress"
at Sejong Center for the Performing Arts?

756
00:40:53,790 --> 00:40:55,260
Yes, that's right.

757
00:40:55,260 --> 00:40:57,750
- Did you play Empress Myeongseong?
- What are you saying?

758
00:40:57,750 --> 00:40:59,230
Were you not the lead?

759
00:40:59,230 --> 00:41:02,240
A court lady. I was a court lady.

760
00:41:02,240 --> 00:41:04,120
I thought you played Empress Myeongseong.

761
00:41:06,550 --> 00:41:09,200
I played a court lady and a dancer.

762
00:41:11,970 --> 00:41:13,900
Look at this cute thing.

763
00:41:13,900 --> 00:41:16,120
- He just made a wish.
- So cute.

764
00:41:16,120 --> 00:41:18,940
- Gosh, it's a cat.
- So cute.

765
00:41:19,790 --> 00:41:22,120
Did you see the cat around the house?

766
00:41:22,120 --> 00:41:23,910
The fat black one?

767
00:41:23,910 --> 00:41:26,070
Look at these two.

768
00:41:26,850 --> 00:41:28,660
- What's this?
- They must be buddies.

769
00:41:28,660 --> 00:41:30,740
They're friends, but...

770
00:41:30,740 --> 00:41:33,910
- How do you know that?
- They're friends, but they fight.

771
00:41:33,910 --> 00:41:36,470
- They fight?
- They keep fighting.

772
00:41:36,470 --> 00:41:39,380
The calico keeps teasing.

773
00:41:39,380 --> 00:41:42,670
But the black one comes over and taps.

774
00:41:42,670 --> 00:41:44,370
They fight like this.

775
00:41:44,370 --> 00:41:47,550
- And he goes away.
- He's a fake friend.

776
00:41:47,550 --> 00:41:51,230
Yes, they love tussling with each other.

777
00:41:51,230 --> 00:41:55,040
He said, "How do you know?"
I love stuff like that.

778
00:41:55,040 --> 00:41:57,580
- Did we digest a bit?
- I totally did.

779
00:41:57,580 --> 00:41:59,720
- Really?
- I want fish cake.

780
00:41:59,720 --> 00:42:02,670
- You're just craving it, aren't you?
- I am.

781
00:42:03,670 --> 00:42:05,910
What do you think
of this court lady's outfit?

782
00:42:06,595 --> 00:42:09,030
- Doesn't it look real?
- It's the real deal.

783
00:42:09,030 --> 00:42:10,960
[Fascinated]

784
00:42:10,960 --> 00:42:14,300
- I can't imagine you at work.
- I'm working today, too.

785
00:42:14,300 --> 00:42:16,510
I do phone consultations sometimes.

786
00:42:16,510 --> 00:42:19,020
Wow, I'm curious.

787
00:42:19,020 --> 00:42:20,960
Let's go to the courthouse now.

788
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:23,760
Hold on. Where's my card?

789
00:42:23,760 --> 00:42:26,780
[He missed the pay station]

790
00:42:28,860 --> 00:42:31,000
Yu Gyeong laughs out loud with him.

791
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:34,950
[Clumsy lawyer]

792
00:42:36,030 --> 00:42:38,420
You've got to be kidding me.

793
00:42:40,250 --> 00:42:41,780
How did that happen?

794
00:42:42,460 --> 00:42:44,030
I'm in shock.

795
00:42:46,930 --> 00:42:48,990
This sure is a long holiday.

796
00:42:48,990 --> 00:42:51,370
That was the reason.

797
00:42:51,370 --> 00:42:52,920
It's so crowded.

798
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:54,500
This is such a relief.

799
00:42:54,500 --> 00:42:56,770
- This is healing for me.
- Me, too.

800
00:42:57,530 --> 00:42:58,560
[A fish cake bar in Haebangchon]

801
00:42:58,560 --> 00:43:00,700
I love fish cake bars.

802
00:43:00,700 --> 00:43:02,810
- I'll sit here.
- Can you smell that?

803
00:43:02,810 --> 00:43:04,800
It's amazing.

804
00:43:04,800 --> 00:43:06,740
I love multteok.

805
00:43:06,740 --> 00:43:09,420
Really? Me, too.

806
00:43:11,240 --> 00:43:14,420
Should we add sea urchins?
Right, you don't like them.

807
00:43:14,420 --> 00:43:16,050
Sorry.

808
00:43:16,050 --> 00:43:18,070
Please be nice.

809
00:43:22,480 --> 00:43:24,440
What surprised you?

810
00:43:25,330 --> 00:43:26,570
What about you?

811
00:43:27,250 --> 00:43:29,990
Are you copying me again?

812
00:43:29,990 --> 00:43:31,280
Beef tartare gimbap?

813
00:43:31,280 --> 00:43:33,890
I want that or...

814
00:43:33,890 --> 00:43:36,520
- Tteokbokki.
- Tteokbokki sounds good.

815
00:43:36,520 --> 00:43:37,250
Should we get it?

816
00:43:37,250 --> 00:43:38,360
- Does it, really?
- It does.

817
00:43:38,360 --> 00:43:40,990
- Yu Gyeong loves tteokbokki.
- Do you like multteok?

818
00:43:42,030 --> 00:43:43,930
I do. I'm from Busan, you know.

819
00:43:43,930 --> 00:43:45,220
That's right.

820
00:43:45,220 --> 00:43:47,470
Busan is known for multteok.

821
00:43:47,470 --> 00:43:49,600
Multteok is my favorite.

822
00:43:49,600 --> 00:43:51,130
I...

823
00:43:51,130 --> 00:43:52,990
What's that?

824
00:43:54,070 --> 00:43:55,390
- What is it?
- What is it?

825
00:43:55,390 --> 00:44:02,580
I was going to buy chocolates or candy,
but I couldn't find any nearby.

826
00:44:02,580 --> 00:44:05,210
It's Valentine's Day.

827
00:44:05,210 --> 00:44:08,670
- Wow.
- What's this? What's this?

828
00:44:09,700 --> 00:44:11,820
[She bought a leaf-shaped bookmark
for Beluga of the Forest]

829
00:44:11,820 --> 00:44:14,590
- Gosh, I love it.
- How attentive.

830
00:44:21,530 --> 00:44:25,830
This reminded me of Beluga of the Forest.

831
00:44:25,830 --> 00:44:28,480
- I love it. I love this kind of stuff.
- Really?

832
00:44:28,480 --> 00:44:30,180
- How nice.
- Thank you so much.

833
00:44:30,180 --> 00:44:33,800
Don't mention it.
I wanted to get you something.

834
00:44:33,800 --> 00:44:36,630
[Feeling touched and taking a picture]

835
00:44:36,630 --> 00:44:38,160
You don't have to use it.

836
00:44:38,160 --> 00:44:40,350
He probably takes bad photos.

837
00:44:41,150 --> 00:44:44,170
- Let's eat this.
- Okay.

838
00:44:44,170 --> 00:44:48,940
[Piping hot]

839
00:44:50,110 --> 00:44:51,420
It's good.

840
00:44:52,110 --> 00:44:55,050
- It's a perfect drinking snack.
- I know.

841
00:45:00,120 --> 00:45:01,800
[Yum]

842
00:45:05,090 --> 00:45:09,770
[Having a glass of sake]

843
00:45:11,040 --> 00:45:15,410
Did you say you find them noticeable?

844
00:45:15,410 --> 00:45:18,200
- You don't, do you?
- I'm totally clueless.

845
00:45:18,890 --> 00:45:22,930
There isn't much time left.

846
00:45:22,930 --> 00:45:27,230
I want to go out with people
I haven't gone out with.

847
00:45:27,230 --> 00:45:29,420
I'm going through a phase of confusion.

848
00:45:29,420 --> 00:45:31,560
It seems like everyone is.

849
00:45:32,700 --> 00:45:38,400
But I'm thinking I'll regret
no matter what decision I make.

850
00:45:41,260 --> 00:45:43,160
Do you tend to regret?

851
00:45:43,160 --> 00:45:44,950
Do you like to regret?

852
00:45:45,760 --> 00:45:48,900
I don't like to, but I do sometimes.

853
00:45:48,900 --> 00:45:51,670
It's an unavoidable thing.

854
00:45:54,360 --> 00:45:57,270
But I should try not to.

855
00:45:57,270 --> 00:46:00,870
I'm the type who regrets a lot.

856
00:46:01,940 --> 00:46:07,710
- But I try to think I did my best...
- The best... Right, right.

857
00:46:07,710 --> 00:46:09,030
[Staring]

858
00:46:09,030 --> 00:46:12,060
Really. Really, I agree with you.

859
00:46:12,060 --> 00:46:13,000
It's all true.

860
00:46:13,000 --> 00:46:15,920
Are you sure you aren't copying what I say?

861
00:46:15,920 --> 00:46:17,320
I think you're right.

862
00:46:17,320 --> 00:46:20,730
We each make the best decision we can make.

863
00:46:20,730 --> 00:46:24,340
- Who doesn't do that?
- I agree.

864
00:46:25,260 --> 00:46:27,700
Regret for the path you didn't take.

865
00:46:27,700 --> 00:46:32,530
You always regret the path you didn't take.

866
00:46:32,530 --> 00:46:35,110
There's nothing you can do about that.

867
00:46:37,340 --> 00:46:38,930
You're right.

868
00:46:43,250 --> 00:46:46,650
I think I'll regret
not getting the cheese later.

869
00:46:46,650 --> 00:46:49,140
- Where did you see that?
- Cheesy fish cake.

870
00:46:49,140 --> 00:46:50,490
- We need to get that.
- I'll eat it at the end.

871
00:46:50,490 --> 00:46:52,240
They're so cute.

872
00:46:53,060 --> 00:46:56,180
[Eating cheesy fish cake to have no regrets]

873
00:46:56,180 --> 00:46:57,410
You had one earlier, too.

874
00:46:57,410 --> 00:46:59,250
You get the cheese later, not at first.

875
00:46:59,250 --> 00:47:01,490
Did you get it? Is it good?

876
00:47:02,340 --> 00:47:04,010
I don't remember what happened in Japan.

877
00:47:04,010 --> 00:47:06,100
Did I say I wanted to cry?

878
00:47:06,100 --> 00:47:08,640
You said you barely managed not to cry.

879
00:47:08,640 --> 00:47:11,940
- You barely held back the tears.
- Did I say that?

880
00:47:11,940 --> 00:47:14,020
I cry so easily.

881
00:47:14,020 --> 00:47:17,460
- I ugly cry.
- Ugly cry?

882
00:47:17,460 --> 00:47:20,270
- I really do.
- Really?

883
00:47:20,270 --> 00:47:23,310
Is there a particular reason?

884
00:47:23,310 --> 00:47:27,800
I think I know why.
I actually knew back then, too.

885
00:47:27,800 --> 00:47:30,100
- Really?
- It's just my guess.

886
00:47:30,100 --> 00:47:32,830
But it didn't really bother me.

887
00:47:32,830 --> 00:47:36,100
She only says stuff like this to Jun Hyeon.

888
00:47:37,550 --> 00:47:40,460
- Huh?
- I'm just saying.

889
00:47:43,060 --> 00:47:47,010
Jun Hyeon is so attractive, by the way.

890
00:47:48,570 --> 00:47:52,620
You must've felt many emotions
since you came here.

891
00:47:52,620 --> 00:47:53,880
Right.

892
00:47:53,880 --> 00:47:56,250
So much so that I can't handle it.

893
00:47:56,250 --> 00:47:58,770
You must feel many things.

894
00:48:01,990 --> 00:48:04,380
Gosh, it's so hard.

895
00:48:05,140 --> 00:48:07,720
It really is. Everything is...

896
00:48:09,030 --> 00:48:11,700
[The deeper the feelings,
the deeper the worries]

897
00:48:11,700 --> 00:48:14,250
But I think...

898
00:48:15,670 --> 00:48:17,670
I'm still...

899
00:48:19,610 --> 00:48:22,580
trying to be honest.

900
00:48:22,580 --> 00:48:23,880
That's true.

901
00:48:23,880 --> 00:48:27,060
But I don't do that with just anyone.

902
00:48:28,220 --> 00:48:31,340
I don't share my feelings with anyone.

903
00:48:34,230 --> 00:48:37,170
I try to be friendly, of course.

904
00:48:37,170 --> 00:48:40,260
I do because you have to be.

905
00:48:42,430 --> 00:48:46,460
But when I talk to others,

906
00:48:49,300 --> 00:48:51,530
I think I'm different.

907
00:48:52,530 --> 00:48:58,100
For Jun Hyeon, this is like
a cry for love at this rate.

908
00:48:59,320 --> 00:49:00,660
Right now, Yu Gyeong is...

909
00:49:00,660 --> 00:49:04,060
- This must make her think, too.
- Yes.

910
00:49:05,890 --> 00:49:09,420
[Clank]

911
00:49:11,620 --> 00:49:15,480
[Today was like a Valentine's Day present]

912
00:49:16,950 --> 00:49:22,550
[Where are their hearts headed?]

913
00:49:22,550 --> 00:49:24,970
I sense a bit of a possibility.

914
00:49:24,970 --> 00:49:27,810
She thinks he's a good guy, at least.

915
00:49:27,810 --> 00:49:29,550
Didn't we see her healing a bit?

916
00:49:29,550 --> 00:49:30,860
- Totally.
- 100%.

917
00:49:30,860 --> 00:49:32,130
It was healing for us, too.

918
00:49:32,130 --> 00:49:34,790
She always feels comforted by Jun Hyeon.

919
00:49:34,790 --> 00:49:40,550
We can see her thinking that
he provides her comfort.

920
00:49:40,550 --> 00:49:43,650
I haven't seen her having
that much fun in a while.

921
00:49:43,650 --> 00:49:45,510
She laughed out loud.

922
00:49:45,510 --> 00:49:49,900
She tried to take a video
of him passing the pay station.

923
00:49:49,900 --> 00:49:52,060
- Right. He's funny.
- Acting clumsy like that.

924
00:49:52,060 --> 00:49:54,500
She definitely has positive feelings for him.

925
00:49:54,500 --> 00:50:00,740
Artists tend to be drawn
to people who appreciate art.

926
00:50:00,740 --> 00:50:05,000
She was surprised to hear
that he likes musicals.

927
00:50:05,000 --> 00:50:09,100
Small things like that must've
added to the positive feelings.

928
00:50:09,100 --> 00:50:12,080
And Yu Gyeong apparently...

929
00:50:12,080 --> 00:50:14,500
listens to my music.

930
00:50:14,500 --> 00:50:15,580
You suddenly like her.

931
00:50:15,580 --> 00:50:18,840
Whoever breaks her heart better watch out.

932
00:50:18,840 --> 00:50:22,560
If anything happens to her, I swear...

933
00:50:22,560 --> 00:50:25,350
She's a fan of mine. Be careful.

934
00:50:25,350 --> 00:50:27,760
[LOL]

935
00:50:28,300 --> 00:50:30,040
I wonder if anyone is there.

936
00:50:30,040 --> 00:50:32,810
I don't think so. We must be the first ones.

937
00:50:32,810 --> 00:50:34,880
[The four return after bowling]

938
00:50:34,880 --> 00:50:36,850
We're home.

939
00:50:36,850 --> 00:50:39,370
- We're the first ones.
- You're right.

940
00:50:40,080 --> 00:50:42,920
- Can you just order it?
- Yes.

941
00:50:42,920 --> 00:50:45,400
Seo Won and Yu Gyeong,
how does tteokbokki sound?

942
00:50:45,400 --> 00:50:47,490
I would love it.

943
00:50:47,490 --> 00:50:52,310
[They decide to eat tteokbokki after bowling]

944
00:50:52,970 --> 00:50:58,000
[Wu Yeol and Min Ju return as well]

945
00:51:00,240 --> 00:51:02,590
[Clap, clap]

946
00:51:02,590 --> 00:51:05,390
You're an amazing driver.

947
00:51:06,170 --> 00:51:09,790
I think you are better
than most taxi drivers.

948
00:51:09,790 --> 00:51:11,690
Taxi drivers?

949
00:51:13,560 --> 00:51:16,400
- They're back.
- Hi.

950
00:51:17,140 --> 00:51:18,820
Hi.

951
00:51:19,820 --> 00:51:21,030
[The tteokbokki set arrived]

952
00:51:21,030 --> 00:51:23,040
The portion is so generous.

953
00:51:23,040 --> 00:51:24,810
Look at that cheese.

954
00:51:25,830 --> 00:51:28,650
It's kind of like dakbokkeumtang*.
(Braised spicy chicken)

955
00:51:28,650 --> 00:51:30,450
That's what it is.

956
00:51:30,450 --> 00:51:32,150
It has to be tasty.

957
00:51:32,150 --> 00:51:37,050
[Tempura and cup rice
are made for tteokbokki]

958
00:51:37,780 --> 00:51:40,520
- Enjoy.
- Enjoy, guys.

959
00:51:41,240 --> 00:51:42,310
[Serious eyebrows]

960
00:51:42,310 --> 00:51:45,410
This must be spicy because of the name.

961
00:51:46,280 --> 00:51:48,950
Their rice cake is the best.

962
00:51:50,180 --> 00:51:51,850
Isn't it spicy?

963
00:51:53,220 --> 00:51:54,630
It's good because it's spicy.

964
00:51:54,630 --> 00:51:56,500
It's so good.

965
00:51:56,500 --> 00:51:57,660
It's really good.

966
00:51:57,660 --> 00:52:00,450
[Big bite]

967
00:52:00,450 --> 00:52:02,690
Hand me the fried fish cake.

968
00:52:04,180 --> 00:52:07,240
What? What happened? Don't sit yet.

969
00:52:07,990 --> 00:52:10,330
I'll take some. What's this?

970
00:52:10,330 --> 00:52:12,910
- What's this?
- Flat dumplings.

971
00:52:12,910 --> 00:52:15,280
Check the chair before you sit, Min Ju.

972
00:52:19,580 --> 00:52:20,280
[Glancing]

973
00:52:22,500 --> 00:52:23,920
[Smiling]

974
00:52:23,920 --> 00:52:26,910
[They're getting deeper into the night]

975
00:52:26,910 --> 00:52:28,140
[Coming over]

976
00:52:28,140 --> 00:52:29,820
[Tap tap]

977
00:52:29,820 --> 00:52:32,010
Yes, she needs to talk to him.

978
00:52:34,110 --> 00:52:36,280
- Wait here.
- What is it?

979
00:52:38,290 --> 00:52:39,560
Here.

980
00:52:39,560 --> 00:52:40,670
- She got him a present?
- What did she get?

981
00:52:40,670 --> 00:52:43,380
- What is it?
- For Valentine's Day.

982
00:52:44,200 --> 00:52:45,640
What is it?

983
00:52:45,640 --> 00:52:47,440
I don't know. Open it later.

984
00:52:47,440 --> 00:52:52,110
Today is February 14th.

985
00:52:52,930 --> 00:52:57,390
That's why I got it.

986
00:52:57,390 --> 00:52:58,820
Open it later.

987
00:52:58,820 --> 00:53:01,090
When? Can't I open it now?

988
00:53:01,840 --> 00:53:03,780
- Sure, you can.
- Really?

989
00:53:03,780 --> 00:53:05,270
Should I open it in front of you?

990
00:53:05,270 --> 00:53:09,670
I couldn't find candy or chocolate.

991
00:53:09,670 --> 00:53:12,690
So, I decided to buy something useless.

992
00:53:12,690 --> 00:53:15,240
- Isn't that the tea room?
- It is. It is.

993
00:53:16,900 --> 00:53:18,570
When did you buy this?

994
00:53:18,570 --> 00:53:20,950
- While I was out today.
- Today?

995
00:53:21,870 --> 00:53:25,000
[Nervous for some reason]

996
00:53:30,040 --> 00:53:33,010
What is it? What is it?

997
00:53:33,010 --> 00:53:35,800
I was like, "I'll take the straw shoe."

998
00:53:37,820 --> 00:53:39,860
[This evening]

999
00:53:42,010 --> 00:53:43,820
[Found something]

1000
00:53:45,320 --> 00:53:46,890
It's a straw shoe.

1001
00:53:46,890 --> 00:53:49,480
As in, "Even a straw shoe has its pair"?

1002
00:53:50,190 --> 00:53:55,060
Do you have a new straw shoe keychain?

1003
00:53:55,060 --> 00:53:57,050
Thank you.

1004
00:54:00,200 --> 00:54:04,000
[She bought a straw shoe keychain
for Wu Yeol]

1005
00:54:05,710 --> 00:54:07,650
I'll put this on my car key.

1006
00:54:08,390 --> 00:54:10,420
Huh? Hold on.

1007
00:54:11,240 --> 00:54:12,740
Does this not come off?

1008
00:54:12,740 --> 00:54:14,390
- One each?
- I know.

1009
00:54:14,390 --> 00:54:15,600
One each?

1010
00:54:15,600 --> 00:54:18,520
- I think it'll come apart.
- I don't know how to do it.

1011
00:54:19,620 --> 00:54:21,550
[Focused]

1012
00:54:21,550 --> 00:54:24,060
Is it weird to have matching ones?

1013
00:54:24,060 --> 00:54:25,770
Does it come out?

1014
00:54:28,190 --> 00:54:30,440
Which one do you want? This one?

1015
00:54:30,440 --> 00:54:32,680
- No, you take that one.
- This?

1016
00:54:32,680 --> 00:54:34,990
- This, too?
- Yes.

1017
00:54:34,990 --> 00:54:37,180
Give me the other one.

1018
00:54:37,180 --> 00:54:38,890
I'll wear it.

1019
00:54:39,510 --> 00:54:41,610
You'll wear it?

1020
00:54:41,610 --> 00:54:43,890
I'll only wear one shoe.

1021
00:54:46,730 --> 00:54:48,460
It's cute, right?

1022
00:54:49,170 --> 00:54:52,470
It's cute. It's too cute.

1023
00:54:52,470 --> 00:54:54,160
You mean, the straw shoes?

1024
00:54:55,160 --> 00:54:56,700
Both.

1025
00:54:57,780 --> 00:55:03,080
[They got matching items, only they share]

1026
00:55:03,080 --> 00:55:05,380
Yu Gyeong has always been devoted.

1027
00:55:05,380 --> 00:55:07,950
Right. It's always been him.

1028
00:55:07,950 --> 00:55:10,240
She was buying a gift for Jun Hyeon,

1029
00:55:10,240 --> 00:55:12,950
but she wanted to give Wu Yeol something

1030
00:55:12,950 --> 00:55:17,660
to let him know that she was thinking of him.

1031
00:55:17,660 --> 00:55:19,890
- Gosh, daebak.
- How nice.

1032
00:55:19,890 --> 00:55:22,550
And ham, too. This is champagne, right?

1033
00:55:22,550 --> 00:55:25,500
So, the night begins.

1034
00:55:25,500 --> 00:55:28,760
It's okay because we didn't shake it.

1035
00:55:28,760 --> 00:55:29,710
[Startled]

1036
00:55:31,240 --> 00:55:32,440
[Embarrassed]

1037
00:55:32,440 --> 00:55:34,640
- It's okay.
- Good job.

1038
00:55:34,640 --> 00:55:37,290
- Nice, nice.
- That woke me up.

1039
00:55:37,290 --> 00:55:38,920
[Got wet from the champagne]

1040
00:55:39,990 --> 00:55:41,430
What do we do? Do you want to change?

1041
00:55:41,430 --> 00:55:42,850
You drank all that?

1042
00:55:42,850 --> 00:55:44,680
I'm full now.

1043
00:55:45,800 --> 00:55:47,640
You drank all of it.

1044
00:55:47,640 --> 00:55:50,150
Hold on. You're beaming like a baby.

1045
00:55:50,930 --> 00:55:52,640
Why are you so funny?

1046
00:55:53,630 --> 00:55:56,200
Cheers.

1047
00:55:56,200 --> 00:55:58,620
[Everyone finally got together]

1048
00:55:58,620 --> 00:56:02,040
